Romain Sevestre, a rail transit engineer from France, has been in China for 17 years. Having witnessed China's efforts in fighting the COVID-19 pandemic over the past three years, he is happy to see the recent adjustments to the COVID-19 response measures as the virus has become less virulent. Romain also points out that after the easing of China's COVID-19 policies, it will be more convenient for people to visit China, and he says everyone is welcomed.